article.headline: Binghamton 66, Hartford 59
article.story: BINGHAMTON, N.Y. -- D.J. Rivera had 24 points, Malik Alvin added 16 and Binghamton rallied past Hartford 66-59 on Monday night. The victory snapped a three-game losing streak for Binghamton (11-7, 4-2 America East). Emanuel Mayben had 10 points and six assists, and Reggie Fuller had 10 rebounds for Binghamton. Jaret von Rosenberg led Hartford (6-13, 2-3) with 12 points, and Michael Turner and Kevin Estes each had 11 points. Hartford led 27-19 at halftime, and the Hawks built the margin to 42-29 on a layup by Morgan Sabia with 11:49 left. But Rivera led the Bearcats on a 12-point run to close the gap to a point. Mayben hit a 3 to tie it at 46-all with 5:37 remaining and sank another from beyond the arc to put the Bearcats up 51-49 with 4:23 to go. Rivera then converted a three-point play, drained a 3 and made two free throws to give Binghamton a 61-51 lead with 2:38 left.
